a0GaOvCfjyE.title: 20 minute Full Body MORNING YOGA Flow ☀️
a0GaOvCfjyE.description:
Wake up with this 20 minute full body Morning Yoga Flow to stretch your neck, shoulders, back, chest, hip flexors, hamstrings & glutes (open for details) ☀️ FREE GIFT: Everyday Morning Yoga Routine: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/am

Rise & shine with this full body morning yoga flow. You’ll set an intention and loosen up your neck, shoulders and spine and set an intention before setting up your Sun B flow with longer ~3 breath holds, then repeating 1 breath 1 movement. You'll finish in savasana with  a nice banana stretch before sealing the practice off with a namaste. Enjoy! 

👉🏼 The Sun B flow that we practice in this video is from the full length 45 minute RISE Morning Yoga Class available in the SarahBethYoga APP: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/join

N9OL12vC9m0.title: 60 minute Full Body Yoga for FLEXIBILITY & STRENGTH
N9OL12vC9m0.description:
Get fit, flexible and happy with this 60 minute Full Body Yoga for FLEXIBILITY & STRENGTH yoga class 💙 Get MORE in the SarahBethYoga APP https://members.sarahbethyoga.com/orders/customer_info?o=80501 (exclusive discount!) 

Boost your confidence and strength as you chip away the excess stone to reveal the masterpiece within. You are a star. You’re here to shine. This is your time. Enjoy this shine themed class with wrist, shoulder, chest & upper back mobility poses to help you release tension and feel lighter, happier and more confident. This class is sequenced using some of the favorite poses from the PEACE FLOW collection and it’s made for Level 2 yogis with fewer cues so we can get right into our flow. Our peak pose in this class is Bird Of Paradise but we have plenty of options on screen for the peak pose and throughout class so you can make the sequence fit your body today. Enjoy other poses like wheel, wild thing, flip dog, skandasana and lots of binds to help open your shoulders. Enjoy!

CHAPTERS:
00:00 Welcome to Yoga

01:00 Warm up
06:00 Sunflowers
07:30 Theme
08:20 Sun A 
15:00 Sun B
29:00 BURN
37:30 Sun C
44:06 Hips
50:30 Cool Down
1:02:05 Namaste

7yjPnhRbcV0.title: 20 minute CHAIR Yoga for Beginners, Seniors & Desk Workers | Full Body Stretch
7yjPnhRbcV0.description:
Use this 20 minute CHAIR Yoga for Beginners, Seniors and Desk Workers anytime for a gentle full body stretch completely supported by your chair. ⭐️ FREE GIFT: 7 day Beginner Yoga Calendar: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/byc

You'll warm up with neck and shoulder stretches and a gentle spinal flow, then move into modified lunges, warriors, and gentle twists all completely supported by your chair. I provide modifications and progressions so you can start in a safe space and work your way up as you get stronger and more flexible with each practice. Great for⁣ beginners, seniors, desk workers, prenatal, postnatal (details below), recovery, and those with low energy and/or low mobility. ⁣

-PRENATAL & POSTNATAL This video & the entire CHAIR collection are Prenatal & Postnatal friendly. Just modify the lunges, warriors, and twists for less intensity and less stretching (it's easy to overstretch when using a chair) ⁣

01:42 Neck, Chest, Back Stretches
04:00 Ankle Stretch
05:00 Hamstring Stretch
06:00 Ankle Stretch (left)

08:00 Chair Lunges, Twists & Warriors Stretch 
13:00 Switch sides 
18:30 Ragdoll fold
21:00 Slowly rise
21:41 Namaste
22:09 Try the 7 day Beginner Yoga Calendar

PdhnNST4d5c.title: 15 minute Yoga for Grief, Loss & Broken Heart 💜 Low Energy Yoga
PdhnNST4d5c.description:
This low energy Yoga for Grief routine is for all levels, including prenatal & postnatal (details below) 💙 FREE GIFT: 25 min Hips Slow Stretch https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/25-minute-hips-slow-stretch

Simply find a place on the floor to rest in these low energy, low effort, relaxing yoga for grief, loss & broken heart poses like supine twists, wind, and savasana. It doesn't sound like much but it might be exactly what you need right now. 

The entire GRIEF Collection (in the SarahBethYoga APP) was created to give you a safe space with emotional support & guidance to gently stretch your aching body while pumping the brakes on the “fight or flight response” so you can rest and relax into your grief process. 

This video is for all levels and modifications are offered throughout so you can adjust the positions to fit your body today. 

*PRENATAL & POSTNATAL* This video & the entire GRIEF Yoga Collection are Prenatal & Postnatal friendly. Prenatally, you will need to modify the supine twists and savasana at the end with milder twists and a side-lying savasana.  Postnatally, this is completely safe, but it is always recommended to get clearance from your doctor before any exercise, and you may need to modify the supine twist if you have Diastasis Recti (show your doctor this video so you both are on the same page)

CHAPTERS: 
00:00 Welcome
00:20 Child's Pose
2:10 Supine Twist R
04:45 Reset Spine & Lower Back
06:10 Supine Twist L
08:15 Wind circles
09:00 Savasana
14:00 Fetal
14:30 Namaste
15:35 Next try the 25 min Hips Slow Stretch

p5Ql-5ZWK8M.description:
Yoga for Grief | Relieve hip, neck & shoulder tension with this low energy, low effort, grief yoga routine. 
💙 FREE GIFT: 25 min Hips Slow Stretch https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/25-minute-hips-slow-stretch

You'll relax into gentle, stretching poses 1-3 minutes each while settling into a safe space to process and understand your grief. You’ll begin with seated poses to ease into your neck, shoulders and hips then work your way into heart openers and a gentle twist. Modifications are offered throughout so you can adjust the positions to fit your body today. 

The entire GRIEF Yoga Collection (in the SarahBethYoga APP) was created to give you a safe space with emotional support & guidance to gently stretch your aching body while pumping the brakes on the “fight or flight response” so you can rest and relax into your grief process.

PRENATAL & POSTNATAL This video & the entire GRIEF Yoga Collection are Prenatal & Postnatal friendly. Prenatally, you may need to modify to create space for your growing belly in the cross, legged fold. Postnatally, this is completely safe, but it is always recommended to get clearance from your doctor before any exercise (show them this video so they have an idea of what you mean by exercise)

ZtTVyKrW3t4.title: 15 minute Yoga for Beginners Weight Loss & Toning 🔥 BURN
ZtTVyKrW3t4.description:
Get on your mat for this simple 15 minute yoga for beginners WEIGHT LOSS & TONING yoga routine 🔥 for a fat-burning beginners yoga workout to tone, strengthen & stretch. 
⭐️ FREE GIFT:  Beginner Yoga Calendar https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/byc

You'll practice basic power yoga poses including properly setting up a lunge and modified planks to help you build core strength, and BURN *I mean tone* your hips, core, back & arms. 

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

CHAPTERS:
00:00 welcome
00:45 Child's Pose
01:57 Swimmers
03:22 Downdog
04:25 Chair Pose
05:16 Crescent Lunge
09:39 Modified planks
11:31 Feel the BURN 🔥
12:50 Low Cobra
14:00 Child's Pose
15:05 Namaste
15:40 Try the FREE 7 day Beginner Yoga Challenge

a7fpPpxbgos.description:

KmoGSER3Nhw.title: 30 minute Full Body Power Yoga Workout | Weight Loss & Toning
KmoGSER3Nhw.description:
30 minute Full Body Power Yoga for Weight Loss & Toning // Gain strength, mobility, body awareness and the powerful breath control called Ujjayi with this traditional Power yoga practice. You'll have fun with challenging sun salutations, balancing sequences and lots of abs! 💙 Get the HIPS SLOW STRETCH: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/25-minute-hips-slow-stretch

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

🙏🏽 WELCOME to your modern day yoga channel by Sarah Beth Yoga where you can find clear & fuss free yoga videos ranging from short 10 minute yoga routines to longer 30 minute yoga practices for all levels to help you get stronger, happier & healthier. 😍 SUBSCRIBE for MORE free yoga: http://bit.ly/sarahbethyoga

WfdQuz2ZVYk.title: 20 minute Power Yoga for Weight Loss & Toning Abs & Arms  | Sarah Beth Yoga
WfdQuz2ZVYk.description:
Use this 20 minute strength & tone yoga workout to tone your upper body, workout your arms, and BURN your abs. Great power yoga workout for weight loss. 🔥 GET THE 5 MIN QUICK ABS: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/5-minute-quick-abs

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

16:46 Floor Bow
17:23 Childs Pose
17:58 Intense Plank Practice
22:00 Cooldown 
26:20 Savasana 
28:35 Namaste
29:17 Deeply stretch your warmed up hips

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

bOE2oaBJdgY.title: 15 minute Hot & Sweaty Yoga Routine 🔥 Power Yoga for Weight Loss & Strength | Sarah Beth Yoga
bOE2oaBJdgY.description:
Enjoy this 15 minute Power Yoga Workout when you're short on time but ready to get HOT & SWEATY. Great Yoga for weight loss, yoga for strength, and full body power yoga workout. 🔥 5 MIN QUICK ABS: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/5-minute-quick-abs

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? qg3xdJv4waU.title: 15 minute Morning Yoga For WEIGHT LOSS 🔥 Fat Burning Yoga Flow
qg3xdJv4waU.description:
This 15 minute Morning Yoga for weight loss Routine is a quick fat burning yoga flow to get you feeling strong and energized! 💙 FREE GIFT: 25 min Hips Slow Stretch: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/25-minute-hips-slow-stretch

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

WELCOME to your "Modern Day Yoga" YouTube channel by Sarah Beth Yoga where you can find clear & fuss-free yoga videos ranging from short 10 minute yoga routines to longer 30 minute yoga practices for all levels to help you get stronger, happier & healthier. 😍 SUBSCRIBE for MORE free yoga: http://bit.ly/sarahbethyoga

It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

B_rXP_bL9jM.title: 20 minute Yoga for WEIGHT LOSS 🔥 Fat Burning Yoga Workout
B_rXP_bL9jM.description:
This 20 minute yoga for weight loss is a fat burning yoga workout that will move your body, sweat & burn calories. 💙 FREE GIFT: 25 min Hips Slow Stretch: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/25-minute-hips-slow-stretch 

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

m756Gz8de4M.title: 15 minute Morning Yoga for Beginners 🔥 WEIGHT LOSS edition 🔥 Beginners Yoga Workout
m756Gz8de4M.description:
Get on your mat for this simple 15 minute morning yoga for beginners 🔥 WEIGHT LOSS edition 🔥 for a fat burning beginners yoga workout to tone, strengthen & stretch. 
⭐️ FREE GIFT: 7 day Beginner Yoga Calendar: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/byc

Practice this 15 minute yoga workout 3x/week until you feel comfortable then move on to a video in the 💙 BEGINNER YOGA PLAYLIST: http://bit.ly/sbyBeginners

BUT LET'S BE CLEAR: Yoga is not a cure. Yoga is a supplement to a healthy lifestyle. Yes you can get into a fat burning heart rate zone, sweat, strengthen & burn ample calories with power yoga and power vinyasa yoga flows, but if you want to lose weight and practice yoga you must accompany the practice with self-care and healthy habits off the mat. Yoga can be a wonderful practice for de-stressing, connecting mind with body, improving body awareness & learning to love yourself. And guess what? You can love yourself and be a work in progress at the same time! The term "Yoga for weight loss" is a high ranking SEO term, as in it is searched a lot. I use the term to reach a wider audience to help people who are looking for a way to lose excess weight and practice yoga at the same time. I know from personal experience how that feels, as I have lost 40 & 50 lbs from both of my pregnancies and the weight didn't just melt off after. It took at least a year of focused effort, exercise, healthy eating, a mild calorie deficit and this exact type of yoga for me to lose the weight and feel strong and confident in my body. So I created these videos to meet the viewers where they are, help them along in their weight loss journey and hopefully teach them self-love, strength & mindfulness along the way. 💙

🔥 FREE GIFT: 5 min Quick Abs: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/5-minute-quick-abs

fExgivwOvKw.title: Yoga Lifestyle Retreat (2015) Puerto Vallarta | Sarah Beth Yoga
fExgivwOvKw.description:
I'm back home after leading 2 yoga retreats in Puerto Vallarta, Mexico at the beautiful Villa Karaway and I'm overflowing with compassion, gratitude and a deep sense of calm. The retreat leading was an unexpected opportunity that was presented to me a few months ago and once I jumped on board everything seemed to completely fall into place. 9 women from all over the world signed up and we got to explore the jungle, ocean, downtown and our deepest selves, all with each other's love and support.

Before the retreats, I was so focused in the prepping to create memorable experiences and share yoga/mindfulness tools with everyone else that I didn't have any expectations for what I would get out of this. Now that it's all over I'm completely blissed out and even surprised at how much I've grown in those 10 days. I learned something from each of these radiant, unique women and gained a deeper connection to myself as a leader, a nurturer, and a student of compassion & mindfulness. I'm so beyond grateful for this experience and opportunity.

I'm very excited for what is to come!

CFGTG8HBe8w.title: How to Hurdlers Pose | Arm Balance
CFGTG8HBe8w.description:
How to Hurdlers Pose. This arm balance, Hurdlers Pose, goes by many names and has many different entries. Try this one today and if it doesn't come easy then pay attention to what your body is demanding. If it's flexibility, then continue practicing the Gentle Hip Opening Routine. If it's strength that your body wants then try the Plank Practice and hold planks every day. You'll get there in no time! (Open for links) 

Watch this first - Intro to Arm Balances: http://youtu.be/OI9VZ_QHO6s

Simple Warm up: http://youtu.be/HQnH6VU2pi8
Gentle Hip Opening Sequence: http://youtu.be/dF7aC8K7POE
Plank Practice: http://youtu.be/GZZgEAAoYkw
Tabata for Core & Shoulders: http://youtu.be/NASTMw3_F8A 

Take your time, and have fun. You'll get there when your body is ready :) 

AVOID: if you have any injuries, joint problems (knees, wrists, elbows, shoulders, or if anything hurts/doesn't feel right. There is no jumping or launching to get into this pose, just balance, flexibility and strength, so be mindful, take your time and listen to your body first. 

🔥 Get the 5 MIN QUICK ABS: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/5-minute-quick-abs

av0xBIV6zYw.title: How to Fallen Angel Pose | Arm Balance
av0xBIV6zYw.description:
Fallen Angel is a beautiful pose that looks like you just fell from the heavens, once you learn it you'll love it! This pose strengthens your core, shoulders and arms. If you're comfortable in Side Crow you're just that much closer to Fallen Angel (open for warm ups & links) 
Watch this first - Intro to Arm Balances: http://youtu.be/OI9VZ_QHO6s

Essential Vinyasa Warm up: http://youtu.be/SB6cFAGj9s0
Power Yoga Moves for Core Strength: http://youtu.be/iA3voFk3qjE
Try your Side Crow: http://youtu.be/Vl30KiYcJeo

Try it during the side crow option in this (23 minute) "Yoga for Detox & Digestion" practice: http://youtu.be/hXUrVvApAVI

AVOID: if you have any injuries, joint problems (knees, wrists, elbows, shoulders, or if anything hurts/doesn't feel right. There is no jumping or launching to get into this pose, just balance, flexibility and strength, so be mindful, take your time and listen to your body first. 

🔥 Try the 5 MIN QUICK ABS: https://www.sarahbethyoga.com/5-minute-quick-abs
